      <methods>
            <methodStep>
                <description>
                    <para>The species registrations were georeferenced using a GPS navigator.</para>
                </description>
            </methodStep>
            <methodStep>
                <description>
                    <para>The species were found visually and photographed if possible.</para>
                </description>
            </methodStep>
            <sampling>
                <studyExtent>
                    <description>
                        <para>The research was conducted in May 2014 - July 2021.
Lukash O.V. took part in determining some species. Some of the expeditions were supported by the NGO &quot;Ukrainian Nature Conservation Group&quot;.</para>
                    </description>
                </studyExtent>
                <samplingDescription>
                    <para>We used reconnaissance and detailed route methods to survey the section of the Desna river valley from the village of Sverdlovka to the village of Rozlioty of Korop district of Chernihiv region and from the village of Sokolivka to the city of Chernihiv (including inner part of the city), as well as - the valleys of its tributaries - Snov (from the village of Tymonovychi, Semenivsky district of Chernihiv region to the village of Karpovychi of the same district and from the village of Elino Snovsky district to the village, Snovsk of the same district), as well as its tributaries - Revna (from the village of Arkhypivka to the village of Orlykivka, Semenivsky district), Rvanets (from the village of Mashove to the village of Zhadove, Semenivsky district), Bilous and Stryzhnia - within the city of Chernihiv.</para>
                </samplingDescription>
            </sampling>
